CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 22, 1959, pg. 20 reads: "Bishop Signs Register - Like all other guests, Bishop John J. Wright was required to sign the visitors' registry when he arrived as "open-house" guest at The House of Mary on Webster Ave. last week. Witnesses, left to right, are Sister M. Cyril, Mrs. Nellie Johnson, Mrs. Lelia Page, Nicole Page, Andrew Johnson, Mrs. Estella Smith, Billy James, Bishop Wright, Clarence Miller, Father Bassompierre, Edward Smith, Mrs. Lillian Dickerson, Clarence Holley, Mrs. Zora Bowman, J.D. Penny and Mrs. Mary L. White. - Harris Photo."[Incorrect cutline with image published by Pittsburgh Courier]
TitMainTitle: Group portrait, from left: Sister M. Cyril, Nellie Johnson, Lelia Page, Nicole Page, Andrew Johnson, Estella Smith, Billy James, Bishop John J. Wright, signing register; Clarence Miller, Father Bassompierre, Edward Smith, Lillian Dickerson, Clarence Holley, Zora Bowman, J.D. Penny, and Mary L. White, gathered in House of Mary, Webster Avenue
